column1: options pagesize=55 linesize=78 compress=yes nocenter sortsize=600M mprint obs=max;
Program: PQA-ARV
Programmer: HC
Purpose: MSM Health Equity Tracker Quality Measures - ARV PDC
PQA-ARV Eligible Population Criteria:
Step 1 - Identify individuals 18+ years of age as of the first day of the measurement year.
Step 2 - Identify individuals with prescription claims for 3+ distinct ARVs (as a single agent or as a combination) each with 2 different dates of service during the measurement year.
Step 3 - Identify individuals with an IPSD from January 1 – October 2 of the measurement year.

Step 4 - Determine each individual’s treatment period. The treatment period is the time period (in days) from the IPSD to the end of the measurement year, death or disenrollment, whichever occurs first.
Step 5 - Identify individuals with a treatment period that is 91+ days during the measurement year.
Step 6 - Identify individuals meeting the continuous enrollment requirement during the treatment period.
Step 7 - Exclude individuals in hospice care at any time during the measurement year.
libname out "&myfiles_root./dua_051142_hch171/PhRMA-MSM/Outputs";
*** Pull drugs of interest;

column2: /* proc sort data=in051142.PDE20_R12008 (keep=BENE_ID SRVC_DT DAYS_SUPLY_NUM PROD_SRVC_ID BN) out=out.PDE20_R12008_sorted; by BENE_ID SRVC_DT; run; */
data out.pde1_arv; set out.PDE20_R12008_sorted; if PROD_SRVC_ID in: (

column1: *** Step 2 - Identify individuals with prescription claims for 3+ distinct ARVs (as a single agent or as a combination) each with 2 different dates of service during the measurement year;

column2: proc sql; create table step2a as select distinct BENE_ID, SRVC_DT, BN from out.pde1_arv; quit;
proc sql; create table step2b as select BENE_ID, BN, count(distinct SRVC_DT) as DOS_CNT from step2a group by BENE_ID, BN; quit;
data step2c; set step2b; if DOS_CNT >1; run;
proc freq data=step2c noprint; table BENE_ID/out=step2d; run;
data step2e; set step2d; if COUNT ge 3; drop PERCENT; rename COUNT=ARV_COUNT; run;
data step2f; merge out.pde1_arv (in=a) step2e (in=b); by BENE_ID; if a and b; run;
/** proc sql; select count(distinct BENE_ID) from step2f; quit; **/

column1: *** Step 3 - Identify individuals with an IPSD from January 1 – October 2 of the measurement year.

column3: by BENE_ID;
var SRVC_DT;
output out=index1 (drop=_: rename=SRVC_DT=INDEX_DT) min=;
where SRVC_DT <= "02OCT2020"d;

column1: *** Step 4 - Determine each individual’s treatment period. The treatment period is the time period (in days) from the IPSD to the end of the measurement year, death or disenrollment, whichever occurs first.
*** Step 5 - Identify individuals with a treatment period that is 91+ days during the measurement year.
*** Step 6 - Identify individuals meeting the continuous enrollment requirement during the treatment period.

column3: ** Bring in death date, set last day of measurement period, identify last mon;
data ce1;

column4: by BENE_ID; if a and b;
if month(INDEX_DT)=11 and PTD_CNTRCT_ID_12 in ('N','0','') then DEC_DT = "30NOV2020"d;

column3: run;

column1: *** Step 1 - Identify individuals 18+ years of age as of the first day of the measurement year and finalize CE cohort;

column2: data pqa1; set in051142.MBSF_ABCD20_R12008; if AGE_AT_END_REF_YR ge 18; keep BENE_ID; run;
data pqa2; merge pqa1 (in=a) ce1 (in=b keep=BENE_ID INDEX_DT ENROLL_END_DT CE_DAYS); by BENE_ID; if a and b; run;

column1: *** Step 7 - Exclude individuals in hospice care at any time during the measurement year;

column2: proc sql; create table hspc1 as select distinct BENE_ID from in051142.HSPCCLMS20_R12008; quit;
data pqa4a; merge pqa2 (in=a) hspc1 (in=b); by BENE_ID; if a and not b; run;

column1: *** OUTPUT - PDE analysis table;

column3: merge pqa4a (in=a) out.pde1_arv (in=b keep=BENE_ID SRVC_DT DAYS_SUPLY_NUM);
by BENE_ID;
if a and b;
if INDEX_DT <= SRVC_DT <= ENROLL_END_DT;
rename BENE_ID=PTID SRVC_DT=DOS_RX DAYS_SUPLY_NUM=DSUPPLY ENROLL_END_DT=POST_INDEX_DT;

column1: PDC Analysis

column2: * Identify highest claim count by a patient in the the study pop;

column3: create table adh_max_rx_clm as
select PTID, count(distinct DOS_RX) as rx_count
from pqa_pde
group by PTID
order rx_count desc;

column2: * Create rx_end_date waterfall for each patient, have to do this because some scripts are 90 days and can overlap with several scripts;

column3: set pqa_pde;
PTID1 = PTID;
format RX_END_DT1 MMDDYY10.;
RX_END_DT1 = DOS_RX + DSUPPLY - 1;
if DSUPPLY = 0 then RX_END_DT1 = DOS_RX;
data adherence&n2. (drop = PTID&n1.);

column4: if PTID&n2. ne PTID then RX_END_DT&n2. = '.';

column3: run;

column2: * Find end dates for treatments first;

column3: set adherence125; /* EDIT MAX RX COUNT NUMBER */
format MAX_RX_END_DT MMDDYY10.;
array RX_END_DT[*] RX_END_DT1-RX_END_DT125; /* EDIT MAX RX COUNT NUMBER */
format LAG_MAX_RX_END_DT MMDDYY10.;
LAG_MAX_RX_END_DT = lag(MAX_RX_END_DT);
DATE_DIFF = DOS_RX - LAG_MAX_RX_END_DT - 1;
LAG_PTID = lag(PTID);
if PTID ne LAG_PTID then do;
end;

column2: * Flag first day of each treatment period;
data adh3a (keep = PTID DOS_RX POST_INDEX_DT LAG_MAX_RX_END_DT);

column3: set adh2;
if DATE_DIFF = . then NEW_TREAT=1; * this is the first treatment in patients study period;
if DATE_DIFF gt 0 then NEW_TREAT=1; * this is the start of every subsequent treatment after the first;
if NEW_TREAT=1;

column2: * This is setting up a reverse lag on DOS and will set rx start and stop dates for each treatment period;

column3: merge adh3a (keep=PTID DOS_RX POST_INDEX_DT rename = DOS_RX =START_RX)
format END_RX MMDDYY10.;
END_RX = END_RX_PRE - 1;
if PTID ne PTID_LAG then END_RX=POST_INDEX_DT;
TIME_PD = _n_;

column2: * Making clean version of treatment table;

column3: set adh3b (keep = PTID START_RX END_RX TIME_PD);

column2: * Put each claim into a treatment period;
proc sql; *using proc sql instead of merge because need many-to-many matching since some patients have multiple treatments;

column3: create table adh_merge1 as
select *
from adh2 as a left join adh_timespan as b
where START_RX le DOS_RX le END_RX;

column2: proc sort data = adh_merge1; by PTID DOS_RX; run;

column3: * truncate script if it goes past f/u period, this is the ANALYSIS table;
data temp1 (keep = PTID DSUPPLY DOS_RX FINAL_END_RX TIME_PD);

column4: if MAX_RX_END_DT gt POST_INDEX_DT then FINAL_END_RX = POST_INDEX_DT;

column3: run;
* Calculate non-overlapping days;
proc sort data=temp1; by PTID TIME_PD DOS_RX; run;
proc means data = temp1 noprint;
run;
data adh_lot2 (keep = PTID TIME_PD LOT);
run;
proc means data = adh_lot2 noprint;
run;
data adh_lot4;
run;
proc means data = adh_lot4 noprint;
run;
** OUTPUT;
data temp_pdc (drop=AGE_AT_END_REF_YR CST_SHR_GRP_CD: STATE_CNTY_FIPS_CD:);

column4: merge ce1 (in=a keep=BENE_ID INDEX_DT ENROLL_END_DT CE_DAYS AGE_AT_END_REF_YR SEX_IDENT_CD RTI_RACE_CD STATE_CODE COUNTY_CD ZIP_CD STATE_CNTY_FIPS_CD: ENTLMT_RSN_CURR CST_SHR_GRP_CD: rename=BENE_ID=PTID)
by PTID; if a and b;

column3: run;
** Final analysis table;
data out.pqa_pdc_arv_2020;

column4: retain PTID INDEX_DT ENROLL_END_DT AGE_GROUP SEX_IDENT_CD RTI_RACE_CD LIS ENTLMT_RSN_CURR STATE_CODE COUNTY_CD STATE_CNTY_CD ZIP_CD COUNTY_FIPS CE_DAYS LOT PDC_RATE PDC_COMP;
